result.execSummary:
The defendant Devin Alexander Dewindt was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Devin Alexander Dewindt is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Devin Alexander Dewindt was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Justice Point Report received and filed.

Defendant Devin Alexander Dewindt in court with attorney Hazel Jean Washington.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State placed negotiations on the record. The court vacates the jury trial scheduled for 2/29/2016 at 10:00 a.m. in Branch 19.


As to Counts 1 & 3:
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered Counts 1 & 3 dismissed.

As to Count 2:
Defendant changes plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.

  Sentencing hearing scheduled for March 23, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
